hom.sense:
kafatahu, (Ḳ,) or kafatahu Eano wajohihi, (Ṣ,) 
aor. _i {yakofitu}, (Ḳ,) inf. n. kafotN; 
and kf-th↓; (TA;) He turned him away, averted him, or diverted him, from his course, or design. (Ṣ, Ḳ.) (You say) kafatahu Eano HaAjatihi He withheld him, restrained him, or debarred him, from the thing that he wanted. (Aṣ.)

One who contends with another in running, or in a race. (TA.) kafiytN, as used in the following trad., in which Moḥammad says, Hub-ibi UilaI-a Aln-isaACu waAlT-iybu waruziqotu Alkafiyta [Women and perfumes have been made objects of love, or pleasant, to me; and I have been supplied with, or have received,, &c.], 
signifies Food by which the body is sustained; or, sufficient to sustain life: or what sustains life: (TA:) or that by which food necessary for the support of life is drawn, or collected, together, (Ḳ,) and properly prepared for use: (TA:) [or the means of acquiring subsistence, &c.:] or coition; 
[meaning power for coition;] so accord. to El-Ḥasan: or strength for coition: or certain food that was sent down to Moḥammad from heaven, of which he ate, and whereby he received strength for coition: he is related to have said, that Gabriel came to him with a cooking-pot called Alkafiytu, from which he derived the strength of forty men in coition: but Ṣgh says, in the TṢ, that the descent of the cookingpot from heaven is not accepted as true by the authors on the traditions. (TA.)

kalaOa 
[unless this be a mistake 
for kl-O↓] He postponed, or delayed, a thing. (TA, art. nasaOa.)

entry.sense:
kiylajapN, (Ṣ, and so accord. to the Mgh and the Mṣb and Es-Sakháwee, TA, but in some copies of the Ḳ kayolajapN,) as also kylqp and kylkp, (Shifà el-Ghaleel,) A certain measure, mikoyaAlN, (Ṣ, Ḳ,) used in El-'Irák, consisting of two menns and seven-eighths of a menn; the menn (man-) being two pounds; 
[consequently, five pounds and three quarters]: (Mṣb:) or half a SaAE: (Az, in Mgh and Mṣb, voce kur-N:) 
[from the Persian kiylaho:] pl. kiylajaAtN (Mṣb:) and kayaAlijN and kayaAlijapN, (Ṣ, Ḳ,) in which last the klH is added because it is a foreign word. (Ṣ.)

kamadN Concealed grief or sorrow: (Ṣ, A, L, Mṣb:) or grief or sorrow which one cannot dispel: (L:) or intense grief; 
as also kamodN↓ 
and kumodapN↓: (Ḳ:) or most intense grief or sorrow: (ISd, L:) and disease of the heart from intense grief or sorrow. (Ḳ.)

Affected with concealed grief or sorrow; 
as also kamiydN↓: (Ṣ, Mṣb:) or, both words, with grief or sorrow which cannot be dispelled: (L:) or, with intense grief or sorrow; 
as also kaAmdN↓ 
and makomuwdN↓ [which see below]: (Ḳ:) or, with most intense grief or sorrow: (L:) and, with disease of the heart from intense grief or sorrow; 
as also kaAmidN↓ 
and makomuwdN↓. (Ḳ.)

Q. 1. kanobava 
and takanobava↓ He became hard and strong: (L:) he became contracted; syn. taqab-aDa: (Ḳ:) [app. in disposition; 
see kunobuvN: or in make; the second verb being also expl. in the L, with reference to a man, by the words tadaAxala baEoDuhu fiI baEoDK].

kahorabN and kahorabaA [or kahorubaA] A well-known yellow substance; [yellow amber]: 
from the Persian kaAhu rubaA, i. e., “carrying off straw,” [on account of its electric attraction]. (TA.) See De Sacy's Chrest. Ar., sec. ed., iii. 468: 
and see HawarN.

